Had the original instruments of homage, under the seals of the parties been still entire, greater certainty in the names and additions of individuals might have been ensured; but these have perished by gradual decay3 and in the royal treasury at the Chapterhouse, little more than some fragments are now to be found, together with a few of the seals which had been, not inappropriately, attached to the writings by strong hempen cords.
